{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Now consider the second-order translation with respect to x 0 of□ i q → □ i □ i q, ∀Q(RO(Q) → ST x 0 (□ i q → □ i □ i q)),which is equivalent to∀Q ∀v(Qv ↔ ∀v ′ ⊑ v ∃v ′′ ⊑ v ′ Qv ′′) → ∀x ⊑ x 0 ∀y(xR i y → Qy) → ∀z(xR 2 i z → Qz),(6.2)using xR 2 i z as the obvious abbreviation.",
    "If we plug in for Q the first-order description of the minimal valuation from (6.1), i.e., for each variable α, replace Qα with ∀w ⊑ α ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′, then we obtain:∀v (∀w ⊑ v ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′) ↔ (∀v ′ ⊑ v ∃v ′′ ⊑ v ′ ∀w ⊑ v ′′ ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′) → ∀x ⊑ x 0 ∀y(xR i y → ∀w ⊑ y ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′) → ∀z(xR 2 i z → ∀w ⊑ z ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′).",
    "(6.3)Every frame satisfies the main antecedent of (6.3), so we can reduce (6.3) to ∀x ⊑ x 0 ∀y(xR i y → ∀w ⊑ y ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′) → ∀z(xR 2 i z → ∀w ⊑ z ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′).",
    "(6.4)Moreover, every frame satisfying R-down satisfies the main antecedent in (6.4), so we can reduce (6.4) to ∀x ⊑ x 0 ∀z(xR 2 i z → ∀w ⊑ z ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′), (6.5) which over frames satisfying R-down is equivalent to the simpler∀x ⊑ x 0 ∀w(xR 2 i w → ∃w ′ ⊑ w xR i w ′).",
    "(6.6)Over frames satisfying both R-down and R-dense, (6.5) is equivalent to the still simpler ∀x ⊑ x 0 ∀w(xR 2 i w → xR i w)."
  ],
